.Im MicroEmacs modes
.so me.tni
.TH line 2m
.XI line - "Line kill policy"
.SH NAME
line \- Line kill policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "line Mode"
.sp
\fBL\fR \- mode line letter.
.SH DESCRIPTION
By default an invocation of
.Ht kill-line 2
at the  left-hand  margin  will  kill the whole  line. If  \fBline\fR  mode is
enabled and the line  contains  text then only the text is killed,  leaving an
empty line. If the line is empty then it is removed.
